Package: insuranceSimModel
Title: Simulate Insurance Exposure and Loss Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Ryan", "Thomas", email = "rthomas2003@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package implements the features of the Casualty Actuarial
     Society's Loss Simulation Model (LSM) completely in R/Shiny. In addition,
     the LSM is extended to include policy listing simulation. The goal of this
     package to provide actuaries and researchers interested in insurance
     losses a tool to investigate analysis techniques on datasets where
     ultimate values of claim counts and loss amounts are already known.
URL: https://github.com/actuarialvoodoo/insuranceSimModel
BugReports: https://github.com/actuarialvoodoo/insuranceSimModel/issues
Depends: R (>= 3.3.1)
License: What license is it under?
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports:
     dplyr,
     lubridate,
     magrittr,
     stringr
Suggests: testthat
